<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,1044,1322]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,1116,1142]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dumeril, Dumeril &amp; Bibron" authorityYear="1854" box="[345,507,1116,1142]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gabonica">
<emphasis box="[345,507,1116,1142]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Bitis gabonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a large-bodied forest adder (
<bibRefCitation author="Barlow, A. &amp; Wuster, W. &amp; Kelly, C. M. R. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Phelps, T. &amp; Tolley, K. A." box="[856,1071,1116,1142]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1234 - 1248" refId="ref33576" refString="Barlow, A., Wuster, W., Kelly, C. M. R., Branch, W. R., Phelps, T. &amp; Tolley, K. A. (2019) Ancient habitat shifts and organismal diversification are decoupled in the African viper genus Bitis (Serpentes: Viperidae). Journal of Biogeography, 46 (6), 1234 - 1248. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jbi. 13578" type="journal article" year="2019">
Barlow 
<emphasis box="[947,1004,1116,1142]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
), known mainly from the forests and savannas of West, Central and East Africa and with a distribution ranging from 
<collectingCountry box="[1100,1167,1152,1178]" name="Benin" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Benin</collectingCountry>
to northern 
<collectingCountry box="[1305,1387,1152,1178]" name="Angola" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Angola</collectingCountry>
and northeastern KwaZulu-Natal (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[529,751,1188,1215]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[633,689,1188,1214]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
for more detail). It is one of five currently recognized species in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ceriaco et al. 2020 c)" baseAuthorityName="Ceriaco" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[333,755,1224,1250]" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Macrocerastes">
<emphasis box="[333,498,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Macrocerastes</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Tolley, K. A. &amp; Marques, M. P. &amp; Heinicke, M. P. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[514,747,1224,1250]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 11" refId="ref35999" refString="Ceriaco, L. M. P., Tolley, K. A., Marques, M. P., Heinicke, M. P. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2020 c) A dwarf among giants: phylogenetic position of the elusive Angolan Adder (Bitis heraldica) and biogeographic affinities of Angolan Afromontane regions. African Journal of Herpetology, 69 (1), 1 - 11. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 21564574.2020.1782484" type="journal article" year="2020">
Ceríaco 
<emphasis box="[610,667,1224,1250]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2020c
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. From the regions in which Newton collected, this species is known from N’dalatando, 
<collectingRegion box="[449,719,1260,1287]" country="Angola" name="Kwanza Norte" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Kwanza Norte Province</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[734,965,1260,1286]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[841,897,1260,1286]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[984,1148,1260,1286]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref37152" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1904) Reptis e amphibios de Angola da regiao ao norte do Quanza (Colleccao Newton 1903). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (25), 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1904">Ferreira (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[1160,1217,1260,1287]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">1906</bibRefCitation>
) did not publish on the aforementioned specimen.
</paragraph>
